Later, he rushed to the front line and, with "a fantastic bravery", paved the way for the soldiers, then attacked an artillery nest on his own and managed to eliminate three of the detachment's weapons.
Lieutenant-Colonel Vann was killed by a German sniper on 4 October 1918, just a month before the end of the war.
Michael Vann, 72, said his grandfather’s actions were “something I know I’ll never be able to match, but that makes me feel humbled.”
